00:23:57.900 --> 00:23:59.867
So he's got two things
he's looking at.

00:23:59.867 --> 00:24:04.633
He's got the radar, and he's
looking at the reflectivity,

00:24:04.633 --> 00:24:06.800
which is telling you where
the rain is falling.

00:24:06.800 --> 00:24:11.233
And in that, he's finding
this shape, which is

00:24:11.233 --> 00:24:12.467
called the hook echo.

00:24:15.967 --> 00:24:18.867
So there's rain falling through
here, and the spin up

00:24:18.867 --> 00:24:23.100
in the cloud is wrapping
this rain shaft around

00:24:23.100 --> 00:24:25.400
in a kind of spiral.

00:24:25.400 --> 00:24:28.000
And that's a very clear
signature of a very strong

00:24:28.000 --> 00:24:30.000
cyclone aloft.

00:24:30.000 --> 00:24:31.700
Then he's also got
the Doppler.

00:24:31.700 --> 00:24:37.933
For the same instrument, the
same radar, it measures the

00:24:37.933 --> 00:24:41.567
frequency of the reflected
radar beam.

00:24:41.567 --> 00:24:44.167
And they know what frequency
they sent out.

00:24:44.167 --> 00:24:47.200
If it comes back a higher
frequency, that means the air

00:24:47.200 --> 00:24:49.700
at that location is moving
towards you.

00:24:49.700 --> 00:24:51.367
If it comes back at a lower
frequency, it's

00:24:51.367 --> 00:24:52.300
moving away from you.

00:24:52.300 --> 00:24:54.500
This is the Doppler effect.

00:24:54.500 --> 00:24:58.033
When a car goes by or a train
goes by, you hear that

00:24:58.033 --> 00:24:59.800
[ZOOMING NOISE]

00:24:59.800 --> 00:25:02.400
as it's coming towards you and
then going away from you.

00:25:02.400 --> 00:25:03.867
There's that frequency shift.

00:25:03.867 --> 00:25:07.100
And what he was showing with
these two regions, one was red

00:25:07.100 --> 00:25:11.367
and one was blue, indicating in
one region the wind is away

00:25:11.367 --> 00:25:14.067
from you, in the other region
it's toward you.

00:25:14.067 --> 00:25:19.633
So it probably was like this
if the radar was down here,

00:25:19.633 --> 00:25:23.500
which means there
is a cyclone.

00:25:23.500 --> 00:25:24.000
On this side its--you're not

00:25:24.000 --> 00:25:25.467
measuring this other component.

00:25:25.467 --> 00:25:27.267
You're just measuring the
component towards and away

00:25:27.267 --> 00:25:28.067
from the radar.

00:25:28.067 --> 00:25:33.100
But when you see that doublet,
that velocity away from you

00:25:33.100 --> 00:25:36.200
and velocity towards you,
there's really only one

00:25:36.200 --> 00:25:37.000
explanation for that.

00:25:37.000 --> 00:25:40.933
There's a tight vortex right in
there up in the cloud, and

00:25:40.933 --> 00:25:45.500
very possibly that's causing
a tornado at the ground.

00:25:45.500 --> 00:25:49.333
So what's nice about that
film loop is that's

00:25:49.333 --> 00:25:50.333
not after the fact.

00:25:50.333 --> 00:25:51.333
That's during the fact.

00:25:51.333 --> 00:25:54.500
So he's putting himself on the
line and saying, listen, I

00:25:54.500 --> 00:25:58.000
know sometimes we have false
